ABUJA – With barely 3weeks to February 26 national convention of the All Progressives Congress (APC) former members of House of Representatives in the All Progressives Congress(APC) have resolved to weigh in on issues and challenges facing the party as the APC navigate to the 2023 General Election. Not to be left out in providing solution to the turbulence in the APC, the former lawmakers have scheduled a Round- Table on Thursday, 3rd, 2022 to discuss critical issues affecting the party. A statement jointly signed by the Protem Chairman of the Forum, Hon Ibrahim Zailani and the Protem Secretary, Hon Idris Yahuza said the purpose of the meeting is ” To discuss The State of our Party, Issues, Challenges and the forthcoming APC National Convention- The Role of Former Members of the National Assembly and the Road to 2023″. Ekiti Governorship Election: Kolawole Receives Certificate Of… Bye-Election: Alade Olanrewaju Lawson Wins APC Primary They therefore urged all Former House of Representatives members in APC to endeavour to attend the meeting in order to be able to aggregate opinions on sundry political issues affecting the party and the nation at large.